{"parentUuid":"b9596e89-eb94-419a-a0d2-37f50e921bca","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01Neb1yPmAGrg6fpwh4otvS6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No — slate/reslate are already first-class in your CLAUDE.md context (Quick Verbs table + gazette wire-format protocol), so a skill would duplicate what's already auto-loaded every session.\n\nSkills earn their keep when (a) the behavior crosses project boundaries — your JJK protocol is repo-specific — or (b) the trigger is fuzzy enough that documentation alone doesn't catch it. Slate/reslate are neither: the verb is unambiguous, the procedure is mechanical, and the existing prose already prevents the common pitfalls (H1 delimiter, single-call gazette lifetime).\n\nThe one case where I'd reconsider: if you find yourself repeatedly correcting an agent that misuses the gazette wire format despite the docs, a skill could enforce the procedure more aggressively. But that's a \"skill as backstop for instruction failure\" pattern — fix the docs first."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":40556,"cache_read_input_tokens":16497,"output_tokens":1363,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":40556,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":6,"output_tokens":1363,"cache_read_input_tokens":16497,"cache_creation_input_tokens":40556,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":40556},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Cb6bYYKzkkLhiHqseKQwu","type":"assistant","uuid":"bfa270db-fb0a-47dd-80ac-01b1e24a5197","timestamp":"2026-05-16T16:53:56.058Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/bhyslop/projects/rbm_alpha_recipemuster","sessionId":"190642fa-49f1-435e-a4cd-f8e5